>---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Victoria Fendel, Robert Crellin\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic-simple-lemmatized\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἐνθάδε\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"ἐνθάδε\">ΕΝΘΑΔΕ\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan data-text=\"ζησασ\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"ζάω\">ΖΗΣΑΣ\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔτη\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"ἔτος\">ΕΤΗ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ν\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"ν\">Ν\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΥΤΟ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":233,"html":234},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>",{"id":236,"html":237},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>  \u003Cspan>Text after Amico and Kaibel\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"1\">1: \u003Cspan>Amico 1741: 274: ΕΝΘΑΚ\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"3\">3: \u003Cspan>Amico 1741: 274: ΕΤΗΝ; Amico 1741: 277: ΕΤΕΝ̅\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"4\">4: \u003Cspan>Amico 1741: 274: ΚΤΩ....; Kirchoff: [τελευτᾷ τῇ πρὸ -- Ὀ]κτω[βρίων]; Ferrua: [ὑπατίᾳ — —ο]υ τὸ[\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":239,"html":240},"translation","\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>",{"id":242,"html":243},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Amico presents the text in two different variants, without seemingly recognising that it is the same text. Ferrua suggests that the traces in line 4 would be compatible with a consular dating, such as for an imperial consul, as with Honorius in 404 CE, but obviously the actual date is speculative. Kirchoff in CIG offered a possible restoration of line 3-4 on the basic of Amico's alternative reading.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":245,"html":246},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 36.0844 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Amico 1741 274, 277 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002186\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002186\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kirchhoff 1877 9500 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001249\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001249\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">558\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Ferrua 1982-1983 27 no.91 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001996\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001996\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":248,"html":249},"handnote"," \u003Cp>lunate sigma and the use of a supraline on numeral recorded by Amico\u003C/p> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":251,"html":252},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[254,256,259,261,264,265,268,269],{"html":255},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag",{"id":257,"lang":104,"html":258},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἐνθάδε\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"ἐνθάδε\">ἐνθάδ[ε\u003C/span>  